WEBVTT

01:46.190 --> 01:48.775
I know maybe a dozen reporters,
guys you know, too,

01:48.859 --> 01:50.443
who tell me they've been
pitching you this story

01:50.527 --> 01:52.320
for almost a year with no luck.

01:52.404 --> 01:55.323
Yeah, I'm not crazy
about being interviewed in print.

01:55.407 --> 01:59.076
Print journalists play it fast
and loose with exclamation points.

01:59.661 --> 02:02.121
"I love the news" becomes "I love the news!"

02:02.206 --> 02:03.915
Suddenly I'm deranged.

02:04.041 --> 02:05.958
- So why now?
- Huh?

02:06.043 --> 02:07.335
Why are you agreeing to this piece now?

02:07.419 --> 02:09.837
- You don't happen to have a cigarette?
- No.

02:09.963 --> 02:12.548
- Why now?
- Ah! Right here.

02:12.674 --> 02:13.925
Why do you want this now?

02:14.009 --> 02:17.053
I want some sort of document
about what we've been trying to do here.

02:17.179 --> 02:19.680
Like the king at the end of Camelot

02:19.765 --> 02:22.809
telling the boy to run behind the lines
from village to village

02:22.893 --> 02:24.143
telling people about, you know...

02:24.228 --> 02:25.645
- Camelot.
- Yeah.

02:25.729 --> 02:27.313
I'm asking why you reached out to me.

02:28.357 --> 02:31.108
Because, your recent
complications notwithstanding,

02:31.193 --> 02:32.777
you cover the media better
than anyone out there.

02:32.861 --> 02:33.861
You haven't lost your touch

02:33.946 --> 02:36.239
for complimenting and
insulting someone at the same time.

02:36.323 --> 02:39.742
Thank you. I appreciate it.
But it wasn't meant as an insult, Brian.

02:39.827 --> 02:41.327
Your life's been in news magazines,

02:41.411 --> 02:43.246
- and news magazines aren't...
- I know.

02:43.330 --> 02:44.705
...as many pages long as they used to be.

02:44.790 --> 02:46.249
What kind of access are we talking about?

02:46.333 --> 02:48.751
Here's what I'll offer.
You spend a few days here,

02:48.836 --> 02:50.962
talk to whoever you want,
but it's all off the record.

02:51.046 --> 02:53.339
- Not even background.
- What good does that do me?

02:53.423 --> 02:55.633
If I like how it feels, then we go ahead.

02:55.717 --> 02:59.679
But I still get to tell you what can retroactively
go on the record from the tryout period.

02:59.763 --> 03:02.473
- You're asking me to audition?
- Yeah.

03:02.599 --> 03:03.933
Why would I do that?

03:04.017 --> 03:05.268
I can think of some reasons.

03:05.394 --> 03:08.187
Four years ago, you were on
the masthead at Newsweek,

03:08.272 --> 03:10.106
turning out 10 cover stories a year

03:10.232 --> 03:12.024
and spending Sunday mornings on TV.

03:12.109 --> 03:13.609
Today you have a blog.

03:13.694 --> 03:15.653
Your fucking disdain for the Internet...

03:15.779 --> 03:18.114
Is matched only by
your fucking disdain for the Internet.

03:18.240 --> 03:20.700
You took a buyout when
Newsweekwas sold to IAC

03:20.784 --> 03:24.287
and rolled the money into a start-up,
thinking you'd be the next Huffington Post.

03:24.371 --> 03:25.371
How'd it work out?

03:25.455 --> 03:26.664
We filed for bankruptcy.

03:26.748 --> 03:31.127
The Sunday Times Magazine, Vanity Fair,
GQ, The New Republic, The Atlantic,

03:31.253 --> 03:34.046
everybody's offered the cover
and I get to pick the writer.

03:34.131 --> 03:36.883
I'm going with New York Magazine and you.

03:36.967 --> 03:39.302
So, you okay with the audition?

03:39.386 --> 03:41.304
Are you prepared to talk
about your Republicanism?

03:41.638 --> 03:42.722
You say that like I've got polio.

03:42.806 --> 03:44.140
Are you prepared to talk about having polio?

03:44.224 --> 03:48.561
I grew up in a town outside a town
outside Lincoln, Nebraska.

03:48.645 --> 03:49.770
My hometown was a road.

03:49.855 --> 03:52.565
I was a college freshman
before I met a Democrat.

03:52.649 --> 03:53.691
What about our history?

03:55.652 --> 04:01.574
Brian, your problem with me back in the day
was that I was a moderate, sane Republican

04:01.658 --> 04:04.660
who refused to take a position on anything
for fear I would lose viewers.

04:04.828 --> 04:06.954
Just as moderate,
sane Republicans on the Hill

04:07.039 --> 04:09.749
refuse to take a position
for fear they'll lose primary voters.

04:09.833 --> 04:12.960
I had a nightly rundown that went out
of its way to avoid reporting the news.

04:13.045 --> 04:17.798
And then MacKenzie McHale came along
and I'm attacking my own party

04:17.883 --> 04:19.675
for not standing up to its attackers.

04:19.760 --> 04:22.345
Isn't that what you wanted me to do
when you were calling me a coward?

04:22.429 --> 04:24.680
Yeah, but that's not
the history I'm talking about

04:24.806 --> 04:27.266
and you already knew that,
so please stop fucking around with me.

04:30.520 --> 04:32.605
One parenthetical sentence
in the second graph.

04:32.689 --> 04:35.191
"Full disclosure.
I've been a friend of MacKenzie McHale's

04:35.275 --> 04:37.234
- "since the late '90s."
- And you?

04:37.319 --> 04:42.239
An email went to 178,000 people
and was reported on our own morning show.

04:42.324 --> 04:44.700
That's all you know
and that's all you'll report.

04:45.869 --> 04:49.288
That's fine with me. But that's the last time
you'll tell me what I will or won't report.

04:49.373 --> 04:52.541
- I'm not your stenographer.
- Do we have a deal?

04:53.293 --> 04:56.045
Yeah, now why do you need someone
to run from village to village?

04:56.129 --> 04:57.296
Is something about to happen to Camelot?

04:57.381 --> 04:58.547
Maybe.

04:58.632 --> 05:01.217
First, you have to learn
what our whole philosophy is.

05:01.635 --> 05:05.471
Hang out, we'll talk later.
I have to go to a meeting with Reese Lansing.

05:05.555 --> 05:07.139
What's it about?

05:07.224 --> 05:09.433
Suspending our whole philosophy.

05:09.518 --> 05:11.727
Good to see you again, Brian.

05:16.608 --> 05:18.150
He should be here any minute.

05:22.239 --> 05:23.531
Sorry I'm late.

05:23.615 --> 05:25.866
All right, I'm not gonna tell you
what to put on the air.

05:25.993 --> 05:28.244
You're not allowed to tell us
what to put on the air.

05:29.287 --> 05:31.664
So I'm just gonna tell you the facts.

05:31.748 --> 05:34.166
You got mugged last week.
You got bludgeoned.

05:34.251 --> 05:37.253
- It's Casey Anthony.
- Hang on, wait. She may just be right.

05:37.379 --> 05:39.338
- We knew we'd take a small hit.
- There's nothing small.

05:39.423 --> 05:42.299
Let me just give you the facts and then
invite you to draw your own conclusion.

05:42.426 --> 05:45.845
Nancy Grace averages 283,000
viewers on HLN.

05:45.929 --> 05:50.516
Her time period competitor, News Night,
averages 960,000.

05:50.600 --> 05:53.686
One week ago, HLN begins coverage
of the Casey Anthony trial

05:53.770 --> 05:57.523
and Nancy's audience increases
to 1.5 million viewers,

05:57.607 --> 06:00.276
while News Night's audience
drops to 460,000,

06:00.360 --> 06:03.320
sending you from second to fifth place
in the course of five days.

06:03.405 --> 06:06.115
A feat I previously thought
was only accomplishable

06:06.199 --> 06:08.826
by the New York Mets.

06:09.411 --> 06:12.163
Whose idea was it to not cover
the Casey Anthony trial?

06:12.247 --> 06:13.664
It was mine.

06:14.082 --> 06:15.958
I think the three of you
should have a vaudeville act.

06:16.084 --> 06:18.878
I'm not kidding.
I'm gonna send you on a fucking tour.

06:19.629 --> 06:21.005
It was hers.

06:21.089 --> 06:24.467
MacKenzie, I've never seen a more
vivid picture of why viewers left,

06:24.593 --> 06:25.926
where they went to and why.

06:26.011 --> 06:27.178
You said why twice.

06:27.304 --> 06:29.096
You chose not to work for PBS.

06:29.181 --> 06:32.349
You chose not to work for NPR.
You have a ratings obligation.

06:32.434 --> 06:34.060
No, you have a ratings obligation.

06:34.144 --> 06:36.145
You're in business with the advertisers.

06:36.313 --> 06:37.521
I'm in business with the viewers.

06:37.606 --> 06:38.939
You just lost their business.

06:45.363 --> 06:46.739
That's all.

06:46.823 --> 06:49.325
Do what you want with the information.

06:52.621 --> 06:55.873
I'll not be taken down by this
psychotic cocktail waitress.

06:55.999 --> 06:58.959
That's right, we just keep playing our game,
wait it out and just...

06:59.044 --> 07:00.586
How long can the trial go on?

07:00.670 --> 07:02.630
I've seen the witness list.
It'll run around six weeks

07:02.714 --> 07:04.590
plus summations plus deliberation.

07:04.716 --> 07:07.093
- We'll never make it.
- That's right, so...

07:07.177 --> 07:09.095
Wait, when you said
we wouldn't be taken down

07:09.179 --> 07:10.888
by this psychotic cocktail waitress,

07:11.014 --> 07:13.599
did you mean we weren't
gonna cave or that we were?

07:13.683 --> 07:16.352
- You're gonna cover Casey Anthony.
- Bullshit we are.

07:16.436 --> 07:18.354
We have the three-day
weekend to gear up for it.

07:18.438 --> 07:19.522
Charlie.

07:19.606 --> 07:21.899
Starting Tuesday,
you'll lead with her in the A block.

07:22.025 --> 07:25.069
Give it 15 minutes and a five-minute reset
on the half hour.

07:25.195 --> 07:27.154
Seriously, I can't tell if you're joking or...

07:27.239 --> 07:28.239
- Did you just hear those numbers?
- Yes.

07:28.365 --> 07:31.033
Half our audience changed the channel
in one week.

07:31.159 --> 07:32.243
- I understand.
- Do you?

07:32.327 --> 07:35.329
- Do I understand math?
- Do you understand that it's unprecedented?

07:35.413 --> 07:37.832
I'm not gonna argue with you
when Will can do it for me.

07:37.916 --> 07:40.376
He's never gonna go for this. Tell him.

07:41.336 --> 07:43.003
Have marketing promo the living shit
out of Casey Anthony.

07:43.088 --> 07:44.130
Oh, my God.

07:44.214 --> 07:46.799
Rename the show "Casey Anthony Night
with Casey Anthony."

07:46.883 --> 07:48.634
- Will, hang on.
- Right here on the Casey Anthony Network.

07:48.718 --> 07:50.427
- Mac.
- 'Cause any second I'm going to wake up

07:50.554 --> 07:53.722
and be back in a room with Don Quixote
and the mission to civilize.

07:53.807 --> 07:54.807
- Listen to me.
- No.

07:54.891 --> 07:55.975
How many drinks were thrown in your face

07:56.059 --> 07:57.351
because you didn't think
people should watch

07:57.435 --> 07:59.520
The Real Morons of South Beach
or whatever the hell it's called?

07:59.604 --> 08:02.356
- It's not the same thing.
- It's exactly the same thing.

08:02.440 --> 08:04.859
It's just worse. A child is dead.

08:04.943 --> 08:07.236
A very troubled young mother
either did or didn't murder her.

08:07.320 --> 08:09.572
Her parents are waiting to find out if
she's going to get the needle,

08:09.656 --> 08:12.825
So thank God for TiVo,
otherwise we wouldn't be able to sit down...

08:12.909 --> 08:14.034
It's news.

08:14.119 --> 08:16.078
Yeah, say that three times
and click your heels.

08:16.163 --> 08:17.663
It's entertainment.

08:17.747 --> 08:20.416
And it's just, just this side of a snuff film.

08:20.584 --> 08:22.042
- Sit down, Mac.
- No, I don't want to sit.

08:22.127 --> 08:24.753
- Do it anyway, please.
- 15 at the top, that's a quarter of the show.

08:24.921 --> 08:26.714
- Mac.
- And five at the bottom for a reset?

08:26.798 --> 08:28.215
Please sit!

08:30.427 --> 08:32.178
- Think I like it?
- I know you don't.

08:32.345 --> 08:35.014
It makes me sick.
There isn't enough bourbon in Kentucky.

08:35.098 --> 08:37.349
Okay? We're in the same place on this.

08:37.517 --> 08:41.020
So, let's be in the same place on this.

08:41.104 --> 08:42.563
We've had ratings dips before.

08:42.647 --> 08:44.857
First of all, not like this. Nothing like this.

08:44.941 --> 08:46.358
Second, I want the debate.

08:46.443 --> 08:48.360
The three of us have talked
about a new debate format

08:48.445 --> 08:50.112
for months and
we're not going to be able to do it

08:50.238 --> 08:51.530
if they don't give us a debate.

08:51.615 --> 08:53.073
- I just really...
- They're not gonna give us a debate

08:53.158 --> 08:55.576
if we're in fifth place.
I want the debate.

08:55.660 --> 08:57.244
I want to fundamentally change the way

08:57.329 --> 08:59.246
we interview presidential
candidates for their job.

08:59.331 --> 09:02.833
If that means we have to be Jerry Springer
for a few weeks, I'm willing to pay that price.

09:02.959 --> 09:05.794
When the going gets tough,
the two of you really man up.

09:05.879 --> 09:10.591
Then go with your principles, Mac, but know
a ratings hit like this is all Leona needs

09:10.675 --> 09:14.136
to fire Will without having to explain why.

09:24.731 --> 09:27.441
- All right.
- You'll do it as classy as you can.

09:28.485 --> 09:30.110
I'll have Will wear a top hat and monocle

09:30.195 --> 09:33.239
while he's showing
pictures of the wet T-shirt contest.

09:37.494 --> 09:39.203
I'm sorry about the outburst in there.

09:39.287 --> 09:42.039
Yeah, I'm not sure it was
all about Casey Anthony.

09:43.792 --> 09:46.335
- How did it go?
- He's doing it.

09:46.461 --> 09:48.295
Then he has to disclose that we were...

09:48.380 --> 09:50.214
I told him one parenthetical
in the second graph.

09:50.340 --> 09:51.882
That's it.

09:52.008 --> 09:53.509
He needs to be seen
as a heavyweight again, Mac.

09:53.635 --> 09:55.427
He's not gonna write a tell-all. You're fine.

09:58.515 --> 10:00.432
Murrow did Person to Person.

10:00.517 --> 10:02.601
Celebrity interviews. It was a deal with Paley.

10:02.686 --> 10:04.353
One for them, one for him.

10:04.479 --> 10:08.107
He interviewed Liberace, Mac,
just so he could keep going after McCarthy.

10:08.191 --> 10:10.609
Those were puff pieces. This is poison.

10:11.152 --> 10:14.363
If we're gonna do this,
let's not pretend we're not doing this.

10:17.409 --> 10:19.827
- Jim Harper.
- Hey.

10:19.911 --> 10:21.453
- Brian Brenner.
- I know.

10:21.538 --> 10:23.789
I wasn't sure if you remembered.
It's been a few years.

10:23.915 --> 10:25.541
Sure. It's good to see you.

10:25.709 --> 10:28.085
Are you looking at BigGoverment. Com?

10:28.169 --> 10:29.670
- Yeah.
- Don't make me write

10:29.754 --> 10:32.631
that you're using Andrew Breitbart
to research this show.

10:32.716 --> 10:35.884
No, we're gonna be doing a mock debate
at the end of next week.

10:36.011 --> 10:37.136
A mock debate?

10:37.220 --> 10:40.139
The RNC is looking at Will
to possibly host a debate,

10:40.348 --> 10:42.975
and Will and Mac
have an idea for a new debate format.

10:43.059 --> 10:45.227
We want to show them,
so we're each playing a candidate

10:45.312 --> 10:48.480
and we're gonna do a mock debate
on Michele Bachmann, so...

10:48.565 --> 10:49.732
- Andrew Breitbart.
- Yeah.

10:50.025 --> 10:52.151
Tell me about this new
debate format you guys want.

10:53.111 --> 10:56.822
You know, I'm not really sure
what I'm allowed to talk to you about yet.

10:56.906 --> 10:58.991
Do you mind if we wait
until I get some instructions?

10:59.075 --> 11:00.117
- Sure.
- Thanks.

11:05.874 --> 11:07.207
Hey.

11:07.292 --> 11:08.542
- Hey.
- I heard you were here.

11:08.626 --> 11:09.752
You're not getting out of town
for the weekend?

11:09.836 --> 11:11.587
- Nope. How about you?
- Yeah.

11:11.963 --> 11:14.298
I'm going to a think tank
conference outside Baltimore.

11:14.382 --> 11:16.759
The Institute For Capital
Studies and Economic Growth.

11:16.843 --> 11:19.511
- It's gonna be a raver.
- I think it's called a rager.

11:19.929 --> 11:21.347
- Are you sure?
- No.

11:21.431 --> 11:23.390
It's either a rave or a rager or a raver.

11:23.475 --> 11:25.976
Don't think the Institute For
Capital Studies and Economic Growth's

11:26.061 --> 11:27.144
gonna be any of them.

11:27.228 --> 11:28.520
So I stopped in to give you a heads up.

11:28.605 --> 11:30.105
I might need a couple extra
minutes Tuesday night.

11:30.565 --> 11:31.607
I don't think I can give it to you.

11:31.691 --> 11:34.026
The House is going to vote
up or down on increasing the debt ceiling.

11:34.110 --> 11:36.487
- It's a cosmetic vote, but...
- If it's a cosmetic vote, why...

11:36.613 --> 11:38.155
It's news because first of all,
it'll be the first time

11:38.239 --> 11:40.949
in history the House lets
the US default on its debt.

11:41.034 --> 11:44.578
But moreover, it'll be the first shot
in the beginning of a very reckless,

11:44.662 --> 11:48.457
extremely dangerous partisan fight
that could end in catastrophe.

11:48.583 --> 11:50.167
- Let me explain.
- I can't give you the time.

11:50.251 --> 11:52.669
- If Congress doesn't raise...
- I can't give you the extra time.

11:52.796 --> 11:56.256
Starting Tuesday, I have
to cover Casey Anthony.

11:58.468 --> 12:00.969
- I really liked that we weren't doing that.
- I really liked it, too.

12:01.096 --> 12:03.263
By putting the debt ceiling
vote in the A block, we'd be sending...

12:03.348 --> 12:06.725
I can't, Sloan.
We lost half our audience last week.

12:06.810 --> 12:09.395
That's not hyperbole.
That's an actual number.

12:09.479 --> 12:11.980
- Half our audience went to HLN at 8:00.
- Half?

12:12.065 --> 12:14.691
If we don't bring them home this week,
we'll have lost most of them for good

12:14.776 --> 12:15.818
and we could lose the debate.

12:17.821 --> 12:20.072
Kenzie, I'm not just trying to get more airtime.

12:20.156 --> 12:21.490
This is an incredibly important...

12:21.616 --> 12:23.659
I had 42 and a half minutes to work with.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.202
I now have 22 and a half.

12:25.495 --> 12:27.079
Do you know how you're gonna
budget the 22 and a half?

12:27.163 --> 12:28.497
Do you know what Tuesday's news is?

12:28.623 --> 12:31.166
We want the debate. That's the prize.

12:31.292 --> 12:34.002
Those guys are studying
on a Friday night of a three-day weekend.

12:34.087 --> 12:36.630
- Okay, next question.
- Congresswoman Bachmann,

12:37.173 --> 12:39.633
you're a proponent of reforming
Social Security and Medicare.

12:39.717 --> 12:41.927
Can you give us some details of the reforms
you have in mind?

12:42.011 --> 12:45.139
I'd start by reducing benefits for all
but current recipients

12:45.265 --> 12:47.307
as part of an effort to
reduce the federal deficit.

12:47.392 --> 12:49.852
I'd like to add that President Obama
has already transferred

12:49.936 --> 12:53.147
over $500 billion out of
Medicare and into Obamacare,

12:53.314 --> 12:55.315
which I will repeal on my first day in office.

12:55.400 --> 12:58.193
Ms. Bachmann, are you aware that presidents
can't repeal laws?

12:59.154 --> 13:01.530
I, Jim, am aware of that, but...

13:01.614 --> 13:02.948
Where are you getting the quote?

13:03.032 --> 13:05.534
BigGovernment. Com. It's right here.

13:08.371 --> 13:09.371
- Hmm.
- What?

13:10.206 --> 13:12.583
Anthony Weiner's Twitter account got hacked.

13:12.709 --> 13:14.543
Can I suggest a way to
turn lemons into lemonade?

13:14.627 --> 13:15.627
Sure.

13:15.712 --> 13:18.005
First you squeeze the juice from the lemons.
Then add sugar and water.

13:18.089 --> 13:19.089
And you're not really into this joke,

13:19.215 --> 13:21.133
so I'm just going to say
what I really wanted to say.

13:21.217 --> 13:23.343
The Casey Anthony story
actually gives us a chance to show

13:23.428 --> 13:25.762
how important the debt ceiling
story is if we lead

13:25.847 --> 13:27.639
with the debt ceiling
instead of Casey Anthony.

13:27.724 --> 13:28.974
When do you have to go to your raver?

13:29.058 --> 13:31.143
- I've got plenty of time.
- Tea, can I have another?

13:31.269 --> 13:33.187
- Yeah.
- Hey, how about Brian Brenner?

13:33.271 --> 13:35.481
I've been reading him for years
and didn't know what he looked like.

13:35.565 --> 13:36.732
- He's cute.
- Yeah.

13:36.816 --> 13:38.275
- Is he single?
- He is.

13:38.359 --> 13:39.818
- Are you interested?
- Nope.

13:40.487 --> 13:42.154
That's contempt prior to investigation.

13:42.238 --> 13:45.324
No, it's contempt after
thorough investigation.

13:45.533 --> 13:47.242
- You dated him?
- I did.

13:47.327 --> 13:49.995
- When?
- About six years ago.

13:50.079 --> 13:51.705
That's... Wait.

13:51.789 --> 13:53.457
- That's...
- Yeah.

13:55.251 --> 13:57.753
Six years ago, you were
with the guy you were with before Will.

13:57.879 --> 14:00.047
Yeah.

14:02.509 --> 14:04.092
- But that would...
- Oh, my God, Sloan.

14:04.177 --> 14:05.636
It's like the land where time stands still.

14:05.720 --> 14:08.180
Brian Brenner is the guy
I cheated on Will with.

14:11.434 --> 14:13.685
I'd been with Will for a year
and Brian started calling me again.

14:15.230 --> 14:16.480
- Wow.
- Yeah.

14:16.564 --> 14:17.940
- Why would he do the piece?
- Brian?

14:18.024 --> 14:19.316
- Yeah.
