Everything's off the record.

29:12.960 --> 29:14.544
Go ahead. What keeps our attention?

29:14.628 --> 29:16.003
Is the bottom right corner
where they're playing

29:16.088 --> 29:18.089
a loop of little Caylee from a home video.

29:18.173 --> 29:21.968
Hell. Do you think
it's as bad as everyone says it is?

29:22.469 --> 29:25.054
That was a tribute to Caylee.

29:25.139 --> 29:28.099
But how will they explain the duct tape

29:28.308 --> 29:30.685
around the child's mouth and nose?

29:30.769 --> 29:32.270
And how will they explain

29:32.354 --> 29:35.398
all the lies that Tot Mom told?

29:35.482 --> 29:37.108
Now they're not talking about the tattoo

29:37.192 --> 29:39.235
on Casey's back, but they put it full screen.
Why?

29:39.361 --> 29:41.028
Because Tess was just about
to look somewhere else,

29:41.196 --> 29:43.364
so they changed the frame
to anything that might keep her attention.

29:43.449 --> 29:45.450
He's right.
I was gonna google Mac's hell question.

29:45.534 --> 29:47.160
Plus tattoo equals bad mom.

29:47.286 --> 29:48.995
No one's ever gone broke
in America serving up

29:49.079 --> 29:50.663
a woman who makes other
women feel superior.

29:50.747 --> 29:52.832
The series of lies

29:52.916 --> 29:55.376
that finally came crashing down around her.

29:55.669 --> 29:56.961
If she would lie about that,

29:57.045 --> 29:59.964
why should I believe an accident is true?

30:00.048 --> 30:02.216
Don't spend time thinking
about her airtight syllogism.

30:02.301 --> 30:04.635
Her EP's showing duct tape and a plastic bag,

30:04.761 --> 30:07.513
so you know you're watching
Miami.

30:07.598 --> 30:09.140
...how to make weapons

30:09.224 --> 30:12.310
out of home materials found in the home.

30:12.394 --> 30:15.062
About breaking necks.

30:15.230 --> 30:16.814
How can they explain that?

30:16.899 --> 30:19.484
They can't explain it, Nancy.

30:19.568 --> 30:22.945
The defense is doing
what the defense has to do.

30:23.780 --> 30:25.406
Now, Bill Sheaffer has done his job.

30:25.491 --> 30:27.783
He agreed with Nancy.
We don't need to see his face anymore.

30:27.868 --> 30:29.911
Look how cute Caylee is.

30:30.204 --> 30:32.413
She deserved better than a mom with a tattoo.

30:32.581 --> 30:34.165
She deserved...

30:35.292 --> 30:37.168
- She deserved...
- Me.

30:37.252 --> 30:38.920
- Me.
- Me.

30:39.004 --> 30:41.464
Tess, how's that Google search coming?

30:41.590 --> 30:43.883
It does look pretty bad. A lot of fire.

30:43.967 --> 30:46.636
You'll notice little of her coverage
in this instance is about the law.

30:46.762 --> 30:48.930
You know, come to think of it,
I did notice that.

30:49.014 --> 30:50.264
It's all based on an emotional appeal.

30:50.390 --> 30:53.100
The way she would with a jury
if there was no judge there to stop her.

30:53.227 --> 30:54.852
Watch how she breaks down
courtroom footage.

30:54.937 --> 30:57.563
Liz, let's see the video of Tot Mom

30:57.648 --> 31:01.526
and Jose Baez back at it in court again today.

31:01.610 --> 31:06.030
Not a good look between
a death penalty defendant

31:06.323 --> 31:08.282
and the lead defense attorney.

31:08.367 --> 31:09.867
Two seconds.

31:10.452 --> 31:13.329
Two seconds of Casey Anthony
walking past her lawyer,

31:13.455 --> 31:15.623
and she'll show it to you in slow motion

31:15.707 --> 31:18.084
and from a different angle

31:18.168 --> 31:20.670
and at regular speed
and from the original angle again.

31:20.754 --> 31:22.964
- What does that remind you of?
- Instant replay in sports.

31:23.048 --> 31:24.382
And she looks pretty pissed at her lawyer.

31:24.466 --> 31:27.009
And that's exactly why she's showing it
to you so many times.

31:27.135 --> 31:29.554
So you have a chance to draw
your own thoroughly uninformed opinion

31:29.680 --> 31:31.305
about an utterly innocuous exchange.

31:31.598 --> 31:33.307
She looks pissed.

31:33.392 --> 31:35.601
"I wonder if she's sleeping with her lawyer.
I bet she is."

31:35.686 --> 31:37.812
"I wonder if that's what she looked like when
she killed Caylee."

31:37.938 --> 31:40.815
"This is the best TV ever. I've got to go
on my Casey Anthony Facebook page

31:40.899 --> 31:43.192
"and see if my Casey Anthony
Facebook friends just saw Casey Anthony

31:43.318 --> 31:45.194
"make a Casey Anthony face
at her Casey Anthony lawyer."

31:45.320 --> 31:47.905
All right, enough.
Will's a criminal prosecutor.

31:47.990 --> 31:50.157
Maybe he can talk about how
our justice system wasn't built

31:50.242 --> 31:51.576
to lock up guilty people.

31:51.660 --> 31:53.202
It was built to keep innocent people free,

31:53.287 --> 31:55.580
which is something Americans
should be proud of and fiercely protect.

31:55.747 --> 31:56.956
No.

31:57.874 --> 31:59.667
He can't ever imply that the viewer

31:59.751 --> 32:01.711
doesn't already know everything
and that she might be innocent.

32:01.795 --> 32:04.589
If we're gonna cover this,
we're gonna cover it our way.

32:04.673 --> 32:06.299
What's the point of covering
it at all unless we do it

32:06.383 --> 32:07.883
in a way that gets our audience back?

32:07.968 --> 32:11.596
A modest proposal.
We could ourselves commit murder on our air.

32:11.680 --> 32:13.806
In your face, Nancy Grace!

32:18.228 --> 32:19.312
How do we get the best guests?

32:19.396 --> 32:22.189
There's a guy you're gonna have to deal
with named Dylan Kagin.

32:22.316 --> 32:24.942
He's like the Broadway Danny Rose
of tabloid suffering.

32:25.027 --> 32:26.152
He's an agent?

32:26.236 --> 32:27.987
You ever ask yourself
why of all the missing kids

32:28.071 --> 32:29.614
and murdered coeds,
most of them go unnoticed

32:29.698 --> 32:31.616
- and some become national scandals?
- Sex appeal.

32:31.700 --> 32:34.827
Right, but someone's got to find
Lana Turner sitting at the drugstore counter.

32:35.120 --> 32:38.205
Dylan Kagin gropes through the trailer park
of American jurisprudence

32:38.290 --> 32:40.082
for what he calls "Oh, my God" stories.

32:40.167 --> 32:42.835
Then he drops in on the victims,
the accused, the jurors, the cops,

32:42.919 --> 32:44.920
whoever he can sell to the press,
the networks, and the studios.

32:45.005 --> 32:46.380
He packages the missing white girl.

32:46.506 --> 32:48.382
All right, that'll be the A block.

32:48.467 --> 32:49.842
By 2:00, show me where we are.

32:49.926 --> 32:51.218
The B block's gonna be Anthony Weiner,

32:51.303 --> 32:53.054
so, Jim, start putting something together.

32:53.138 --> 32:55.806
All we really have are the pictures
and Weiner not answering questions.

32:55.891 --> 32:58.100
- I know that.
- You don't want to wait until we have...

32:58.226 --> 33:00.519
Facts? No, that would be newsy and elitist.

33:00.604 --> 33:04.732
Let's just call them the A and the B block.
Let's just think of them as a polished,

33:04.816 --> 33:06.442
tightly produced abomination.

33:06.526 --> 33:08.736
I've been sitting here
and I'm getting a little sick of this.

33:08.904 --> 33:10.363
- You and me both.
- Jesus Christ.

33:10.447 --> 33:13.240
For a few weeks, we're not gonna
ask the country to eat its vegetables.

33:13.325 --> 33:15.576
Why? Because there's a debate we want to do

33:15.702 --> 33:18.371
that trumps all of your Sarah Lawrence
ethical conundrums.

33:18.455 --> 33:20.164
It shouldn't be too hard to understand.

33:20.290 --> 33:22.375
So get it the fuck together.

33:25.253 --> 33:26.545
He happens to be right.

33:26.672 --> 33:28.798
"War on drugs a failure."

33:29.800 --> 33:32.093
I know how it feels.

33:35.555 --> 33:37.264
Show me where we are at 2:00.

33:38.266 --> 33:40.935
- Mac, can I see you a second?
- Yeah.

33:52.572 --> 33:54.990
- Do you mind if I sit in on...
- Yeah, sorry, no.

33:56.243 --> 33:58.285
Not sure that's the best way
to get good press.

33:58.370 --> 34:01.080
May 1 st, the night we got bin Laden,
I got a call

34:01.164 --> 34:03.541
from an anonymous source at 7:30

34:03.625 --> 34:05.543
telling me the White House
would send an email blast

34:05.627 --> 34:08.045
to all the news agencies in 90 minutes,

34:08.130 --> 34:10.965
and obviously it turned out he was right.

34:11.133 --> 34:13.843
He was demonstrating his credibility.

34:13.927 --> 34:15.553
His name is Solomon Hancock.

34:15.637 --> 34:18.639
He works in software engineering at the NSA

34:18.765 --> 34:20.683
and he handed me a stack of documents,

34:20.767 --> 34:23.769
transcripts of his testimony
describing illegal surveillance.

34:23.854 --> 34:25.896
We have to start vetting
him and the documents.

34:25.981 --> 34:28.023
It's gonna take at least a few days,
but that's part one.

34:28.108 --> 34:29.275
What's part two?

34:29.359 --> 34:31.819
If we air his story, he'll give us evidence

34:31.903 --> 34:34.822
that TMI! 's been doing the same thing
as News of the World.

34:37.242 --> 34:38.617
- Hacking?
- Everything.

34:38.702 --> 34:41.579
- TMI! 's been hacking?
- Hancock says he's got the proof.

34:41.830 --> 34:43.998
Jesus Christ.
How high does he say it goes?

34:44.499 --> 34:45.499
Reese.

34:47.127 --> 34:49.086
- Let's get on with the vet.
- I'll have Jim run it.

34:49.171 --> 34:50.921
- Is he up for this?
- He is, Will.

34:51.006 --> 34:52.506
I taught him how to do the news.

34:52.591 --> 34:55.050
I taught them all how to do the news.

34:56.219 --> 34:57.428
Can you give us a second?

34:58.346 --> 34:59.430
I'm done.

35:04.394 --> 35:06.228
Why did it have to be Brian?

35:07.189 --> 35:09.774
Because I own him now.
He needs a cover story.

35:09.858 --> 35:13.527
If he writes a negative one, he'll get slammed
with the whole soap opera of our history.

35:13.987 --> 35:15.279
Are you lying right now?

35:15.363 --> 35:17.239
- Anything else?
- Yeah.

35:17.991 --> 35:21.535
Sloan says on Thursday, the House
is gonna vote to default on our loans,

35:21.620 --> 35:24.288
leading to a global economic meltdown.

35:24.372 --> 35:28.375
Should I put that before or after
Anthony Weiner in his underwear?

35:30.504 --> 35:32.963
I'm sure you'll figure it out.

35:41.223 --> 35:42.640
That's all for us tonight.

35:42.724 --> 35:44.558
Tomorrow we'll be bringing
you all the highlights

35:44.643 --> 35:47.561
from day seven of the trial
and Detective Yuri Melich,

35:47.687 --> 35:51.232
the first officer to interview
Casey Anthony in 2008.

35:51.316 --> 35:53.943
Terry Smith is coming up from Washington
with The Capital Report.

35:54.069 --> 35:55.236
I'm Will McAvoy.

35:55.320 --> 35:58.113
Good night.

36:06.748 --> 36:10.167
Will McAvoy,
your new choice for Casey Anthony coverage.

36:10.252 --> 36:11.752
- They're coming home.
- Yeah?

36:12.128 --> 36:13.420
We promoed the hell out of it.

36:13.505 --> 36:15.422
We got 150,000 viewers back.

36:15.507 --> 36:18.259
25-54, almost all women.

36:18.343 --> 36:20.553
That's toasters, furniture, food, clothes,

36:20.637 --> 36:22.680
kids' clothes, vacation plans.

36:22.764 --> 36:25.307
Our heads are above water now,
so do not stop.

36:25.433 --> 36:27.017
- We won't.
- How about this heat?

36:27.102 --> 36:29.144
- Yeah.
- 9:00 in the morning, it's already 87.

36:29.229 --> 36:31.105
It's gonna hit 98.
That would beat the record for this day

36:31.189 --> 36:34.024
- that was set in 1933.
- Yeah.

36:34.234 --> 36:35.734
- You're looking at me funny.
- Yeah?

36:35.819 --> 36:38.279
- I know you hate this.
- I'm looking at you the regular way.

36:38.446 --> 36:39.738
- If you say so.
- I do.

36:39.823 --> 36:42.825
There are also tornado warnings.

36:42.909 --> 36:45.661
- Reese.
- What?

36:46.037 --> 36:48.080
- Nothing.
- All right, so it's gonna get up to 98.

36:48.164 --> 36:51.458
That's a record. And there are tornado
warnings for New York City.

36:51.585 --> 36:53.669
Well, you know, Aunt Bee,
tornadoes are just God's way

36:53.753 --> 36:55.629
of destroying property and killing people.

36:55.755 --> 36:57.172
People like hearing about extreme weather.

36:57.257 --> 36:59.216
We're not doing a fucking
weather report, okay?

36:59.301 --> 37:01.093
We're not coming up with
some "Tornado Watch" graphic.

37:01.177 --> 37:02.636
We're a serious news organization.

37:02.721 --> 37:05.931
Tonight we'll be reporting on the killer
cocktail waitress and the congressman...

37:06.057 --> 37:08.225
- Is Mac bitching at you?
- Not nearly as much as she should be.

37:08.310 --> 37:11.228
I came in here to tell you
you got back 150,000 viewers

37:11.313 --> 37:12.813
you lost while you were trying to be above it.

37:13.273 --> 37:14.648
We'll be sure not to try that again.

37:14.774 --> 37:16.734
98 degrees is when we have power outages.

37:16.860 --> 37:18.402
Wait a second. Wait a second.

37:18.486 --> 37:20.362
I don't want to go all
conspiracy theory on you,

37:20.447 --> 37:22.823
but I think the heat might
be related to power outages.

37:22.991 --> 37:25.784
- Take it easy.
- Say hi to your mom.

37:26.828 --> 37:28.829
Will do.

37:29.539 --> 37:32.458
Visiting hours will be Tuesday and Friday.

37:32.792 --> 37:34.710
Don't be nervous.

37:37.672 --> 37:40.716
We got 150,000 viewers back last night.
Mostly women.

37:40.800 --> 37:42.217
- I know.
- I was telling her.

37:42.302 --> 37:45.054
You know, it's gonna get up to 98 degrees.

37:45.138 --> 37:46.847
Next person who tells me
about the damn weather...

37:46.932 --> 37:48.098
Do you know what you're doing here?

37:48.183 --> 37:50.225
I've been asked to tell you about the weather.

37:50.310 --> 37:53.354
Does it feel to you like anyone in this room
is in the mood for a joke?

37:54.272 --> 37:55.314
It absolutely does not.

37:55.398 --> 37:57.566
We want you to lead
the vetting of this source.

37:57.651 --> 38:00.861
He's telling us about illegal
surveillance at the NSA.

38:00.946 --> 38:04.990
He's also telling us that TMI! Is in the
same game as News of the World.

38:06.201 --> 38:07.242
Jesus.

38:07.327 --> 38:09.161
We're looking at
a couple of scenarios, Jim.

38:09.245 --> 38:11.747
One is that we're sitting on a scoop
that could shake up the NSA

38:11.873 --> 38:13.832
and maybe have the country
take another look at the Patriot Act.

38:13.917 --> 38:15.960
But the TMI! Element, doesn't that...

38:16.044 --> 38:18.379
Another is that someone's
trying to discredit us

38:18.463 --> 38:20.005
by having Will get Dan Rather-ed.

38:21.091 --> 38:25.135
You'll need to file a couple of hundred
Freedom of Information Act requests

38:25.220 --> 38:27.554
and you'll need to get into
this guy's personal life

38:27.639 --> 38:30.015
and you'll need to do it all

38:30.100 --> 38:33.102
without raising any flags at the NSA.

38:33.561 --> 38:35.062
Are you up for this?

38:39.234 --> 38:42.361
- Yeah.
- We don't need it fast, we need it right.

38:42.445 --> 38:44.822
- But we need it fast.
- I'll start mapping it out.

38:44.906 --> 38:46.573
Jim, since the day you started working here,

38:46.658 --> 38:49.326
I never felt the need
to remind you about confidentiality

38:49.411 --> 38:51.036
and I don't feel that need now.

38:55.500 --> 38:57.459
Okay.

39:06.511 --> 39:07.970
- Gotcha.
- Oh, God.

39:08.346 --> 39:10.222
- You feel like being interviewed?
- You read my mind.

39:10.306 --> 39:12.016
I can't think of anything
I'd rather do right now

39:12.100 --> 39:14.018
than be interviewed by my ex-boyfriend,

39:14.102 --> 39:15.352
except maybe eat my desk.

39:15.437 --> 39:17.438
- It seems like a bad week to be here.
- It is.

39:17.522 --> 39:20.774
I came here to write a story about how Will
and News Night changed overnight.

39:20.942 --> 39:22.693
- And then you changed overnight.
- Look.

39:22.777 --> 39:25.029
- The old Will all over again.
- These are extraordinary circumstances.

39:25.113 --> 39:26.947
That's what everyone says
when they abandon their principles.

39:27.115 --> 39:29.616
I'm no longer required
to live up to your standards.

39:30.744 --> 39:33.120
- Fair enough.
- Thank you.

39:36.249 --> 39:38.125
What's so special about this debate?

39:38.209 --> 39:39.960
If we get what we want,
no one will ever go back.

39:40.045 --> 39:41.545
We'll have changed the debates forever.

39:41.629 --> 39:44.631
And your concern is that if your ratings
are low, you'll lose leverage?

39:44.716 --> 39:47.134
- Yes.
- Is that your concern or Will's concern?

39:47.302 --> 39:48.844
Will's concerns are my concerns.

39:48.970 --> 39:51.972
'Cause another way of looking at it
is that he lost his invisible friends

39:52.098 --> 39:54.391
to Nancy Grace
and he's using the debate as an excuse

39:54.476 --> 39:55.642
to dumb the show down.

39:55.727 --> 39:58.437
That's a pretty bold statement from
a guy who's auditioning for a job.

39:58.521 --> 40:00.814
He's gonna give me the job,
and it's not like I don't know why.

40:01.191 --> 40:03.817
- Do you?
- I do because I'm not a fucking moron.

40:04.152 --> 40:06.236
The email that was read
by everyone in the world,

40:06.321 --> 40:09.531
"I cheated on Will."
You were talking about me, right?

40:13.036 --> 40:14.036
Yes.

40:14.120 --> 40:15.746
You were seeing Will while we were together?

40:15.830 --> 40:17.831
If you count drunk dialing me
at midnight and saying,

40:17.999 --> 40:20.834
"Just come on over and crawl into bed"
as being together, then yes.

40:21.127 --> 40:22.503
- I count it.
- Then yes.

40:22.587 --> 40:23.837
You cheated on me with Will?

40:23.922 --> 40:26.590
Let's be as clear as anyone
has ever been about anything.

40:26.674 --> 40:28.842
I cheated on Will with you.

40:29.010 --> 40:30.177
And I'm paying the price.

40:30.303 --> 40:32.346
I work 30 feet from the life I could have had

40:32.430 --> 40:33.931
if I hadn't been so stupid.

40:34.015 --> 40:35.974
And you're looking at
the life you could have had

40:36.101 --> 40:38.018
if you hadn't been a douchebag.

40:42.190 --> 40:44.066
How's the interview going so far?

40:45.068 --> 40:47.027
Is douchebag one word or two?

40:47.112 --> 40:49.113
Come in.

40:50.532 --> 40:52.449
- Sorry, I can come back.
- No, what do you need?

40:55.203 --> 40:58.705
Well, there's a story I'd like to pitch.

40:58.957 --> 41:01.792
Brian, this is Neal Sampat.
Neal writes Will's blog.

41:01.876 --> 41:04.378
- Will doesn't write Will's blog?
- Will can't find Will's blog.

41:04.879 --> 41:07.381
Neal wants to be a producer,
so from time to time,

41:07.465 --> 41:09.842
he pitches stories. What do you got?

41:10.218 --> 41:11.426
You know what a troll is, right?

41:12.053 --> 41:13.846
A tiny creature that stands under a footbridge

41:13.930 --> 41:16.223
and makes you answer a riddle
before you're allowed to pass.

41:16.307 --> 41:18.183
- They're not real, man.
- I know that.

41:18.268 --> 41:19.560
He means the other kind of troll.

41:19.644 --> 41:21.812
You don't have the first clue what he means.

41:22.480 --> 41:23.772
I mean the other kind of troll.

41:23.857 --> 41:25.149
A little backup would have killed you?

41:25.233 --> 41:27.651
Sorry, Internet trolls.
It's a play on a fishing term.

41:27.777 --> 41:28.819
People who go to message boards

41:28.903 --> 41:30.988
and try to hijack the conversation
by being incendiary.

41:31.072 --> 41:33.198
- What about them?
- Turns out they have their own websites.

41:33.283 --> 41:35.742
Like an online clubhouse.
And to be accepted into the group,

41:35.827 --> 41:37.953
you have to be able to point
to a successful incident of trolling,

41:38.037 --> 41:41.081
a recent time when you made
a whole bunch of posters lose their minds,

41:41.166 --> 41:43.876
or better yet, got the site
monitor to shut down the board.

41:44.294 --> 41:46.795
Actually, I like it.
And it's not about bigfoot.

41:46.880 --> 41:49.256
Write this down, News Night
is gonna break the story on bigfoot.

41:49.507 --> 41:52.176
We're not. Don't write that down.
Will they talk to you?

41:52.260 --> 41:55.429
They won't talk to a reporter,
but I thought maybe I'd try to get in there.

41:55.513 --> 41:58.891
Undercover? Aren't you gonna
have to say you trolled something?

41:58.975 --> 42:01.435
I'm not gonna have to say it,
I'm gonna actually have to do it.

42:01.519 --> 42:03.020
To who?

42:03.313 --> 42:06.481
Well, I don't want to ding on
an innocent person for a story,

42:06.566 --> 42:07.608
so I'm gonna have to do it to one of us.

42:07.775 --> 42:09.109
You'd have to be anonymous on our website.

42:09.235 --> 42:10.527
No, I mean do it to us on another website.

42:10.612 --> 42:13.155
- What would it be?
- I don't know yet.

42:13.239 --> 42:15.908
Come back when you know,
but you've made it past the first hurdle.

42:17.035 --> 42:18.994
Thank you.

42:21.456 --> 42:23.040
- Sloan.
- How's her mood in there?

42:23.124 --> 42:26.376
It's not good, but let me ask you something.

42:26.461 --> 42:27.961
For the sake of a story,

42:28.588 --> 42:31.965
how would you feel about me going on
the Internet and saying vicious things

42:32.050 --> 42:34.259
about you that might get an argument
started about misogyny?

42:34.344 --> 42:37.054
- What kind of vicious things?
- I don't know.

42:37.138 --> 42:39.431
- What would the general area be?
- I really don't know.

42:39.515 --> 42:42.184
- Something about the way you look?
- Like what?

42:42.268 --> 42:44.478
- I'd be making it up.
- What would you be making up?

42:44.562 --> 42:47.606
It wouldn't be true. It'd be something like...

42:47.732 --> 42:50.692
Something along the lines of,
"She screwed her way to the top

42:50.985 --> 42:53.612
"and she's got a big ass."
Only it would have to be...

42:53.696 --> 42:54.947
Listen to me, Sampat.

42:56.866 --> 42:58.659
- Do I?
- Of course not.

43:01.496 --> 43:04.122
Okay.

43:04.207 --> 43:05.624
- I can do it?
- You cannot.

43:06.042 --> 43:07.834
If you want, you can say that
I made it to the final round

43:07.919 --> 43:10.045
of the K-through-six regionals
in the Scripps Howard Spelling Bee.

43:10.129 --> 43:12.839
That's not gonna help me.

43:13.007 --> 43:16.176
You know, a lot of guys like women with big...

43:17.303 --> 43:18.929
Do they really?

43:19.013 --> 43:20.138
Never mind.

43:20.223 --> 43:24.184
I don't know what you're talking about
and I have my own problems.

43:29.524 --> 43:30.899
- Jim.
- Yeah?

43:30.984 --> 43:32.567
I got a woman on the phone
who says she's got some tweets

43:32.652 --> 43:34.152
from Anthony Weiner and wants to talk to us.

43:34.654 --> 43:36.822
- What are you telling me for?
- Seniority?

43:36.906 --> 43:40.158
Well, I'm handing her off to
the next most senior person.

43:40.243 --> 43:41.785
Kendra, take the Weiner girl.

43:41.869 --> 43:44.037
- Gary, take the Weiner girl.
- Tess.

43:44.205 --> 43:47.416
- Tamara.
- We were hired as interns the same day.

43:47.500 --> 43:50.335
I was hired in the morning. You were hired
after lunch. Take the Weiner girl.

43:50.420 --> 43:52.129
Please, don't make me
take the Weiner girl.

43:52.213 --> 43:53.714
Respect the seniority.

43:53.840 --> 43:55.799
Who do I have seniority over?

43:57.510 --> 43:59.011
Maggie.

44:01.222 --> 44:03.515
- Can people still see me?
- On five.

44:09.147 --> 44:10.981
Hi, this is Margaret Jordan.

44:11.065 --> 44:13.191
I'm an associate producer at News Night.

44:13.276 --> 44:15.736
Okay, can you spell that for me?

44:16.904 --> 44:18.947
Okay, wait.

44:19.032 --> 44:20.032
Hang on.

44:20.116 --> 44:22.409
No, you're gonna get a chance.

44:25.038 --> 44:28.081
Well, you certainly seem to
want to share your story.

44:29.751 --> 44:31.668
You really can't just drop in on a doctor.

44:31.753 --> 44:34.004
- What if it's an emergency?
- You go to the emergency room.

44:34.088 --> 44:36.089
They don't have
psychiatric emergency rooms.

44:36.174 --> 44:38.300
They should. You're a good reason why.

44:38.885 --> 44:41.470
- You want a piece of me?
- Seriously?

44:41.554 --> 44:43.555
- No.
- Yeah.

44:47.852 --> 44:49.227
Does he look over at the red light?

44:49.312 --> 44:50.520
Does he look every few minutes?

44:50.605 --> 44:53.565
If I was your therapist,
I'd definitely look every few minutes.

44:54.776 --> 44:56.068
Hey, hey, you can't do that.

44:56.152 --> 44:58.528
It's okay. He likes me.

44:59.781 --> 45:00.906
- Will.
- I'm sorry.

45:00.990 --> 45:02.491
- I'm with a patient.
- I really just need a second.

45:02.575 --> 45:05.369
I'm glad to see you back here, but you
need to come during your appointment.

45:05.453 --> 45:06.453
I could be dead by then.

45:08.706 --> 45:09.998
Are you having suicidal thoughts?

45:10.083 --> 45:11.166
- No.
- Then why did you say that?

45:11.250 --> 45:13.877
- Just to get your attention.
- I'm going back to my patient.

45:13.961 --> 45:16.380
Listen to me.
I've been paying 250 a session for four years

45:16.464 --> 45:17.756
without showing up to a single session.

45:17.840 --> 45:19.841
You owe me $100,000 worth of therapy.

45:19.926 --> 45:22.677
I'll forgive the debt, we'll be totally square,
just give me one minute.

45:26.474 --> 45:28.892
I'm sorry. I'll be just a minute.

45:30.436 --> 45:32.270
You caved for the money.
I'm kind of disappointed.

45:32.397 --> 45:35.315
I didn't cave for the money.
You're getting the sessions you paid for.

45:35.400 --> 45:37.484
You seem like you're in pain.

45:37.819 --> 45:40.404
- He is.
- He said "in pain," not "a pain."

45:40.488 --> 45:41.822
Oh. Never mind, then.

45:43.282 --> 45:44.241
What is it?

45:44.325 --> 45:47.119
I'm doing all these things that are wrong
because of ratings,

45:47.203 --> 45:49.371
and I'm making the staff do things
that they don't want to do,

45:49.497 --> 45:53.125
I'm cursing them out, I'm ignoring incredibly
important news stories,

45:53.251 --> 45:55.043
and I'm betraying the trust
of people who respect me.

45:55.169 --> 45:57.379
And I did it all in the blink of an eye.

45:57.463 --> 45:59.548
- That can be traumatic.
- No, I'm fine with all of that.

45:59.674 --> 46:01.842
Here's my thing. New York Magazine

46:02.009 --> 46:04.261
is gonna do a story on my show
and I get to choose the writer.

46:04.345 --> 46:07.973
And I could have chosen anybody
and I chose MacKenzie's ex-boyfriend.

46:08.683 --> 46:10.142
Of course.

46:10.601 --> 46:13.353
- The one she cheated on you with?
- Yeah.

46:13.521 --> 46:15.272
- Why?
- That's what I came here to ask you.

46:15.356 --> 46:17.566
You're holding your hand over the candle.

46:17.650 --> 46:18.608
What do you mean?

46:18.693 --> 46:22.737
You're holding your hand over the candle
because you think the trick is not minding.

46:24.532 --> 46:25.574
Ahh.

46:25.658 --> 46:28.743
So if I just get through this, I'll be fine.

46:28.870 --> 46:30.912
- No.
- Why?

46:31.205 --> 46:33.123
Because the trick isn't not minding.

46:33.207 --> 46:36.084
The trick is forgiving MacKenzie.

46:36.169 --> 46:38.044
It would be easier
to hold my hand over the candle.

46:38.129 --> 46:39.838
I know.

46:40.506 --> 46:43.884
Well, you've been no help at all, but thanks.
Sorry to barge in.

46:43.968 --> 46:45.802
You know, while you're
working your way through this,

46:45.887 --> 46:47.387
you're hurting MacKenzie.

46:48.806 --> 46:49.806
I know that.

46:51.392 --> 46:53.643
Show up for your appointment.

46:58.316 --> 46:59.733
I'm not doing it on purpose.

47:04.197 --> 47:05.489
Maggie.

47:07.074 --> 47:09.075
Yeah.

47:12.788 --> 47:13.955
- Sandy?
- Yes.

47:14.040 --> 47:16.249
- Margaret Jordan. We talked on the phone.
- Nice to meet you.

47:16.459 --> 47:17.667
- You got here okay?
- Yes.

47:17.752 --> 47:20.003
I have a receipt for the cab.
Who do I give that to?

47:20.087 --> 47:21.755
I'll take it.

47:23.382 --> 47:26.218
So, you got some tweets
from Congressman Weiner.

47:26.302 --> 47:28.512
And I've got copies of them right here.

47:32.600 --> 47:34.267
"'I like the cute new pics of you.

47:34.352 --> 47:36.061
"'Where'd you get those abs? '

47:36.187 --> 47:39.272
'Glad you like them.
When do I get to see your swimsuit shot? '

47:39.899 --> 47:42.776
'When are you coming to see me?
Or just coming? '

47:43.194 --> 47:44.861
'Make me an offer.'

47:44.946 --> 47:47.197
'My door's always open. Get it? '

47:47.281 --> 47:49.241
'What's your plan for us? '

47:49.325 --> 47:52.786
'To get us in the mood,
we watch The Daily Show and Colbert.

47:52.870 --> 47:54.663
"'Then when we're really hot,
we go to the bookstore

47:54.747 --> 47:56.414
"'and replace all the copies
of Glenn Beck books

47:56.582 --> 47:59.125
"'with The Audacity of Hope.
Or, if that's not your thing,

47:59.210 --> 48:01.503
"'we can just get drunk and fuck."'

48:08.302 --> 48:09.594
Why are you doing this?

48:09.679 --> 48:11.346
Because the world needs to know
what kind of guy he is.

48:11.681 --> 48:15.350
It sort of seems like you
were a willing participant.

48:15.476 --> 48:16.893
I didn't know about the other women.

48:16.978 --> 48:18.645
- Did you know he was married?
- Of course.

48:19.272 --> 48:21.481
I just didn't know about the other women.

48:21.732 --> 48:25.443
I was fooled and I think the world needs
to know what kind of guy he is.

48:25.820 --> 48:28.989
By any chance, have you heard
of a guy named Dylan Kagin?

48:29.615 --> 48:30.991
He's gonna be my agent.

48:31.951 --> 48:33.827
Sandy... Can I call you Sandy?

48:33.953 --> 48:35.328
Sure.

48:35.413 --> 48:38.790
Sandy, the congressman is in a lot of trouble.

48:38.874 --> 48:40.166
He got himself into it

48:40.251 --> 48:43.336
and he's probably not gonna
be able to get out of it.

48:45.256 --> 48:48.341
Are you sure you want to pile on?

48:49.302 --> 48:51.761
I think people need to know
what kind of person he is.

48:51.846 --> 48:53.597
All right.

48:55.933 --> 48:58.101
Would you like to be on our show tonight?

48:58.185 --> 49:00.687
That's the thing.
I'm doing Access Hollywood, ET, and Fox.

49:01.063 --> 49:03.315
The big three. No problem.

49:03.482 --> 49:06.067
We can do a pre-tape in a few minutes.

49:06.235 --> 49:08.153
You're a lifesaver.
I was hoping you'd say that.

49:08.237 --> 49:10.196
No kidding? Stay here

49:10.364 --> 49:13.867
and I'll talk to my EP and we'll get this going.

49:13.951 --> 49:15.619
Could I possibly get a decaf latte?

49:15.745 --> 49:19.497
You cannot possibly get that,
but I'll have someone bring you a coffee.

49:26.047 --> 49:28.506
Well, I left it for you
on the left side of the desk.

49:28.591 --> 49:31.217
And, yes, I signed it. Here you go.

49:31.802 --> 49:33.011
I don't know anything about it.

49:33.095 --> 49:35.430
Leona!

49:35.723 --> 49:37.015
A word?

49:37.099 --> 49:39.267
Okay, ask her to show it to me on the plane.

49:40.770 --> 49:42.937
Let's not stand in the street.

49:43.564 --> 49:46.358
Charlie, with that bow tie,
you look like a balloon salesman.

49:46.442 --> 49:48.693
No, I get in the car and get out a minute later,

49:48.778 --> 49:52.906
it looks like we're talking about a problem
or making a drug deal.

49:54.116 --> 50:00.246
We're gonna stand here, smile and nod,
and do this and laugh.

50:02.416 --> 50:04.959
We know where the tabloid stories
are coming from.

50:05.795 --> 50:07.212
They're coming from reality.

50:07.296 --> 50:10.256
Only if you define reality as fantasy,

50:10.383 --> 50:12.550
and they're appearing
in a magazine you own.

50:12.677 --> 50:14.928
How would it look if I had
one of our news magazines

50:15.054 --> 50:16.638
go soft on our flagship anchor?

50:16.764 --> 50:19.349
We're calling TMI! A news magazine?

50:19.433 --> 50:21.976
People need to know if Taylor Swift is happy.

50:22.103 --> 50:23.937
I provide a public service
for hundreds of thousands.

50:24.021 --> 50:25.730
The public's grateful.

50:25.815 --> 50:28.441
What did I tell you
the day after election night?

50:28.776 --> 50:32.612
Friend to friend,
I'd stop coming after Will in the tabloids.

50:32.863 --> 50:36.616
I told you to get him to lighten up
on the Tea Party

50:36.742 --> 50:40.829
or a context would be created
whereby his firing would look reasonable.

50:40.913 --> 50:43.915
- You need to hear me.
- I don't think I do.

50:44.083 --> 50:45.709
The 112th Congress wasn't even seated

50:45.793 --> 50:49.129
and he took the Tea Party out for a walk
on the 9/11 Responders Bill.

50:49.255 --> 50:52.507
Congress, Democrats and Republicans

50:52.633 --> 50:56.010
spent eight years using 9/11 as a justification

50:56.137 --> 50:58.722
for everything from tax cuts
to a foreign invasion.

50:58.806 --> 51:02.058
So Will questioned their change of heart

51:02.143 --> 51:04.477
when it came to the police
and firemen's unions.

51:04.562 --> 51:06.646
You made them look like hypocrites.

51:07.022 --> 51:08.273
By rolling tape.

51:08.357 --> 51:13.820
House Financial Services, insider trading,
Keystone XL, Joe Walsh, Allen West,

51:13.946 --> 51:16.406
Paul Ryan, and who am I forgetting?

51:16.866 --> 51:20.493
Oh, yes. Charles and David Koch.

51:20.911 --> 51:22.328
Keep smiling.

51:22.413 --> 51:24.831
We lost a couple of
awfully helpful tax loopholes

51:24.915 --> 51:26.791
that were tailored to assets overseas.

51:26.876 --> 51:30.211
And the FCC won't even let us bid
on the coming spectrum auction

51:30.463 --> 51:32.255
because they want a full report
on whether or not

51:32.339 --> 51:34.174
we're skirting antitrust.

51:36.093 --> 51:38.344
So what was your request again?

51:38.429 --> 51:40.555
You don't want to do this.

51:41.348 --> 51:43.433
I don't.

51:43.517 --> 51:44.934
I really don't.

51:45.019 --> 51:46.728
But I have to and I will.

51:46.812 --> 51:49.898
And friend to friend,

51:50.274 --> 51:53.109
you let him know that he is
one tabloid fuck-up

51:53.194 --> 51:56.529
and a ratings point away
from having his own podcast.

51:57.782 --> 52:00.033
I have to make my plane.

52:05.664 --> 52:07.373
Fly safe.

52:22.932 --> 52:25.058
- Unless there's a rally...
- I'm sorry, I've got to...

52:25.142 --> 52:26.226
- Listen.
- Sloan.

52:26.352 --> 52:27.977
Unless there's a rally in the next 90 minutes,

52:28.062 --> 52:33.024
the Dow's gonna close down about 2.5%,
S&P and NASDAQ will close down 2.3.

52:33.108 --> 52:35.068
- Let me tell you why.
- I don't own a lot of stock.

52:35.152 --> 52:36.361
- Let me tell you why.
- I really can't...

52:36.445 --> 52:37.946
Stop avoiding this!

52:38.030 --> 52:39.697
I just got off the phone with these guys.

52:39.782 --> 52:42.033
Listen to these quotes.
These aren't from liberals.

52:42.117 --> 52:44.953
These are hardcore Wall Street guys
who, whatever the world may think of them,

52:45.079 --> 52:46.996
know what they're talking about and so do I.

52:47.873 --> 52:49.415
Jamie Dimon at Chase says,

52:49.500 --> 52:52.502
"Voting against raising the debt ceiling
would be a moral disaster."

52:52.586 --> 52:56.214
The Barclays guys say,
"This debate is detached from reality."

52:56.382 --> 53:00.385
My Goldman source says, "If the
House Republicans continue this debate,

53:00.469 --> 53:05.431
"I hope they're willing to mark the end
of the dollar as a global reserve currency."

53:05.641 --> 53:06.850
Please notice that he didn't say

53:06.934 --> 53:09.602
"If the House Republicans
don't raise the debt ceiling."

53:09.728 --> 53:13.606
He said, "If the House Republicans
continue this debate."

53:15.609 --> 53:18.319
That's all it takes.
Just the uncertainty.

53:18.404 --> 53:22.615
That's why the Dow's gonna
close down 230 points today.

53:22.700 --> 53:25.326
Because just the debate, just the doubt,

53:25.411 --> 53:27.912
just the possibility that the House Majority
might commit

53:28.038 --> 53:30.498
the most self-inflicted damage to the country

53:30.624 --> 53:35.086
since the secession of the South
has caused billions in value to disappear.

53:35.170 --> 53:37.255
Sloan, I understand. I swear to God I do.

53:37.339 --> 53:39.173
But you can't say the same
thing in the C block?

53:39.258 --> 53:40.884
You know that most
people watch 10 minutes of news,

53:40.968 --> 53:42.886
- the first 10 minutes.
- The vote isn't until tomorrow night.

53:42.970 --> 53:45.013
And it's only the first vote.
You said yourself it was cosmetic.

53:45.139 --> 53:46.306
Why do we have to feature it tonight?

53:46.432 --> 53:47.640
We should have been featuring it weeks ago.

53:47.808 --> 53:49.851
Why do we have to feature it tonight?

53:49.977 --> 53:52.145
To give time for the people
to call their congressmen

53:52.271 --> 53:56.149
and say, "If you fuck with the full faith
and credit of the US Treasury, you're fired."

53:56.567 --> 53:59.903
To give time for the people to jam
the phone lines of the district offices.

53:59.987 --> 54:02.238
To give the people time to say,

54:02.740 --> 54:03.948
"I'm a fiscal conservative

54:04.033 --> 54:07.535
"and you've got to put the pin back in
the grenade right now."

54:08.454 --> 54:09.996
That's why.

54:13.167 --> 54:15.168
I'm gonna do everything I can.

54:15.502 --> 54:17.420
Please do.

54:23.302 --> 54:24.802
Don't worry about it.

54:24.887 --> 54:27.055
She's just frustrated because
she can't get the word out

54:27.139 --> 54:29.515
that this is a global
emergency unless you let her.

54:31.977 --> 54:34.604
Appreciate your clearing that up.

54:34.688 --> 54:36.397
You know what, MacKenzie?

54:38.484 --> 54:40.443
I'm not the one who put me here.

54:40.527 --> 54:43.446
Say what you want about me,
but I wouldn't have done that.

54:56.752 --> 54:58.086
Does Will have the questions?

54:58.170 --> 55:00.046
Tess is giving him some cards now.

55:03.550 --> 55:05.718
- Is that lighting okay for you?
- Yeah.

55:05.803 --> 55:08.096
- How are we Chyroning her?
- I was gonna ask you.

55:09.348 --> 55:11.140
Figure it out later.

55:15.980 --> 55:17.647
- Sandy.
- Yes?

55:17.731 --> 55:20.441
My name's MacKenzie. I'm the executive...

55:22.653 --> 55:24.445
I'm the executive producer of News Night.

55:24.571 --> 55:26.322
- Can you hear me okay?
- Yes.

55:26.407 --> 55:29.242
Okay. Thanks for being patient with us.

55:29.326 --> 55:33.705
Will's just throwing on a jacket and tie
and we'll be able to do this.

55:34.540 --> 55:37.041
- Real easy.
- You got it.

55:47.845 --> 55:49.012
Hi, I'm a big fan.

55:50.431 --> 55:51.431
Hmm?

55:51.515 --> 55:52.557
I'm Sandy.

55:52.641 --> 55:54.767
How do you do?

55:55.144 --> 55:57.228
- Are we ready for the pre-tape?
- Yeah.

55:57.354 --> 55:59.105
- Just count me down.
- Will.

55:59.189 --> 56:01.315
Yes, I'm sure I want to do this.

56:01.442 --> 56:04.902
God, please give me a sign
I'm not doing a big thing badly.

56:12.036 --> 56:13.161
We just lost power.

56:13.287 --> 56:15.621
The whole building just lost power.

56:15.873 --> 56:18.249
I didn't know he had
that kind of comic timing.
